<TR BGCOLOR="" ALIGN="CENTER"><TD ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" colspan="2"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#ffffff"><b>page 1/16</b><br><b>(entries 1 - 2 of 31)</b></font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="center" colspan="2"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#ffffff"><b>page</b> <b>(1)</b> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=2"><b>[2]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=4"><b>[3]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=6"><b>[4]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=8"><b>[5]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=10"><b>[6]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=12"><b>[7]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=14"><b>[8]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=16"><b>[9]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=18"><b>[10]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=20"><b>[11]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=22"><b>[12]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=24"><b>[13]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=26"><b>[14]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=28"><b>[15]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=30"><b>[16]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=2"><img src="/news/gfx/next.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" title="next page" alt="next page"></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=30"><img src="/news/gfx/last.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" title="last page" alt="last page"></a> </font></td></tr><tr><td width="2%" height="100%" align="center" bgcolor="">&nbsp;</td><td align="center"><table width="100%" align="center" bgcolor="" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td align="left" bgcolor=""colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#ffffff">02/15/2003 07:23:18</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#708090"><td align="left" colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3" color="#FFFFFF">More RETARDED customer service! Scientists prove GM\'s negative IQ values!!!</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="left" colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#ffffff">WE ALL know how much VT crashes on KB. I\'m not talking about once a week or so. This place crashes 5-6 times per day on KB.<BR><BR>So far, most of the times VT crashed, Gm\'s have been helpful with letting us start where the crash had cut off. I\'m not talking about once or twice, i\'m talking about every day of VT, this crashing shit happens 3 or 4 times. I have already posted a rant about this, now on page 4 of the news.<BR><BR>Here\'s a fucking clue, vi - we don\'t give a damn about your retarded crashing server - nor we care about your stupid policies, nor we give a shit about the fact that you employ clearly brain damaged chipmunks as customer service reps that play with corpses like soccer balls - If a zone crashes, especially as much as this one does, its surely SOE\'s fault and noone else\'s. SOE should then do ALL THEY CAN to let it damage the least to their customers. Here\'s my conversation with the two oh-so-smart and helpful GM\'s.<BR><BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:05:51 2003] Felthius shouts, \'Greetings - GM Felthius here.  Please stay clear of the pile of corpses as I need to rez them.\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:06:04 2003] You told felthius, \'hi, i\'m the leader of cr\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:06:36 2003] Felthius tells you, \'Inc CSR rez\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:06:38 2003] You told felthius, \'are we going to get restored to miniaten room / warders depopped?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:09:00 2003] You told felthius, \'cause you see,this zone\'s been crashing lots. We can\'t get to aten ever, unless every time it crashes we get put back where we were\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:09:21 2003] Felthius tells you, \'I\'m sorry but I have to bring you to a known safe locatioin.\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:09:46 2003] You told Felthius, \'yeah thats fine for ressing, but then you need to bring us back where we were =p\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:10:05 2003] You told Felthius, \'and kill all bosses up to miniaten\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:11:58 2003] You told Felthius, \'if you just ress at zone, and do nothing after, that\'s quite poor i\'m afraid to say\'<BR><BR>no answer from felthihus - and someone else shows up..<BR><BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:17:25 2003] Teatraux says out of character, \'if you sttill need a rez send me a tell.\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:17:35 2003] You told teatraux, \'you\'re a gm?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:18:08 2003] You told teatraux, \'i\'m the leader of CR. I\'d like a word with you if so\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:18:26 2003] Teatraux regards you indifferently -- he appears to be quite formidable.<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:18:26 2003] You are inspecting Teatraux.<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:18:27 2003] Teatraux tells you, \'Shoot\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:18:59 2003] You told Teatraux, \'well, firstly, why are we getting ressed at zone?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:19:25 2003] Teatraux tells you, \'This is the zones safe coordinates\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:19:26 2003] You told Teatraux, \'instead of where we were, as it happens with every VT crash (and this zone crashes several times a day in here)\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:20:07 2003] You told Teatraux, \'yes yes i know all that, however we\'ve had the zone crash on us about 20 or more times\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:20:12 2003] Teatraux tells you, \'All I know is I came to finish up the rezzes that were strated by the pvious GM\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:20:25 2003] You told Teatraux, \'previous gm who didnt even contact me before moving corpses around\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:21:06 2003] You told Teatraux, \'if you leave it at this, the customer service will be very poor\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:21:24 2003] You say to your guild, \'tell teatraux if u need a ress/summon/somethin\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:22:27 2003] You told Teatraux, \'also, what about all the people who went to bed after waiting 1h to get someone here?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:23:46 2003] Teatraux tells you, \'I cannot speak for what heppaned in the past but the GM was told to pull the corpses here, as far as the foks who chiose not to wait they can petiton when they come back online.\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:24:03 2003] You told Teatraux, \'you\'re a guide or a gm?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:24:20 2003] Teatraux tells you, \'I am a GM \'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:24:33 2003] You told Teatraux, \'allright\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:25:02 2003] You told Teatraux, \'are you going to kill ktxad/dxv/dxxt/tvk/dxvt/vxahr and let us resume there tomorrow?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:28:30 2003] Teatraux says out of character, \'Does anyone still need a rez? Send me a tell if you do please.\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:32:12 2003] You told teatraux, \'allright, you are not even listening to the issue. What\'s the name and email of your superior please?\'<BR>[Sat Feb 15 06:34:49 2003] You told teatraux \'[queued], did u get synyr\'s corpse?\'<BR><BR>Here\'s the deal, I don\'t know why these gm\'s feel so powerful they don\'t even need to listen to me - but i want to speak with whoever\'s the head of customer service - and i want to speak with them..within tomorrow. God help kelethin if i don\'t get contacted soon and the whole VT issue solved. It is absolutely retarded to waste hours of my guild\'s time like this - only cause of a very known crashing problem. Fix that, and fix the gm incompetence. Make the customer service actual service instead of making gm\'s doing the minimum they can and ignore customers, and i\'ll be nicer to you aswell. I\'d be more talkative if i didnt write all this before, its in the news archive. God save kelethin...if he can</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="left">&nbsp;</td><td align="right" colspan="2"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#ffffff"><a href="#top"><img src="/news/gfx/pagetop.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" title="goto top of page" alt="goto top of page"></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="2%" height="100%" align="center" bgcolor="">&nbsp;</td><td align="center"><table width="100%" align="center" bgcolor="" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td align="left" bgcolor=""colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#ffffff">02/12/2003 22:38:45</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#708090"><td align="left" colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3" color="#FFFFFF">One god at a time...</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="left" colspan="3"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#ffffff">We're still in farm mode, <!-- SPCode Start --><B>Ssra Emp</B><!-- SPCode End --> and <!-- SPCode Start --><B>Cursed</B><!-- SPCode End --> are primary targets and die every time they show their faces. We also continue our weekly <!-- SPCode Start --><B>VT</B><!-- SPCode End --> farm runs, and we're still gearing up for the big challenge that PoP is, but since last week we've also started going full force in PoP killing gods!<BR><BR>Terris Thule died last week as our first target, and today we bring you Vallon Zek:<BR><BR><!-- SPCode Start --><IMG SRC="http://www.kane-bayle.com/gallery/images/57.jpg" BORDER="0"><!-- SPCode End --><BR><BR>And on we go with the exploration!</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="left">&nbsp;</td><td align="right" colspan="2"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#ffffff"><a href="#top"><img src="/news/gfx/pagetop.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" title="goto top of page" alt="goto top of page"></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=""><td align="center" colspan="2"><font face="Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#ffffff"><b>page</b> <b>(1)</b> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=2"><b>[2]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=4"><b>[3]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=6"><b>[4]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=8"><b>[5]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=10"><b>[6]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=12"><b>[7]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=14"><b>[8]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=16"><b>[9]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=18"><b>[10]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=20"><b>[11]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=22"><b>[12]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=24"><b>[13]</b></a> <a class="pagenav" href="/news/news.php?lang=en&amp;layout=orig&amp;category=0&amp;start=26"><b>[14]